==== Immune Profiling

    - Extended flow cytometry panels:
        - T cell subsets: naive (CD45RA#super[+]CCR7#super[+]), central memory, effector memory, TEMRA, exhaustion markers (PD-1, CTLA-4, LAG-3)
        - B cell subsets: naive, memory, plasmablasts, CD21#super[lo] atypical memory
        - NK cell subsets: CD56#super[bright] vs.\ CD56#super[dim], cytotoxicity markers
        - Monocyte subsets: classical, intermediate, non-classical
        - T regulatory cells: CD4#super[+]CD25#super[hi]FoxP3#super[+]
    - Recent thymic emigrants (CD31#super[+] naive CD4 T cells)
    - NK cell cytotoxicity functional assay
    - T cell proliferation assay
    - Cytokine production capacity (intracellular staining after stimulation)
    - Autoantibody panel: GPCR autoantibodies, ANA, anti-neuronal antibodies
    - Inflammatory markers: high-sensitivity cytokine panel (30+ cytokines), CRP, ESR

